
---


@startuml
'---------------------
' Classes
'---------------------

class WebPortal {
  - version: String
  - url: String
}

class Building {
  - id: String
  - name: String
  - energyClass: String (A, B, C, D)
  - address: String
  - yearOfConstruction: Integer
  - owner: User
  - additionalEntries: List<Entry>
  - images: List<Image>
  - profilePhoto: Image
}

class User {
  - username: String
  - email: String
  - password: String
  - activated: Boolean
}

class Administrator extends User {
  - idCardNumber: String
}

class Entry {
  - name: String
  - content: String
  - isPublic: Boolean
}

class TextEntry extends Entry {
  - type: "Text"
}

class NumericEntry extends Entry {
  - value: Float
  - unit: String
  - type: "Numeric"
}

class Image {
  - filename: String
}

class Comment {
  - content: String
  - author: User
  - building: Building
}

'---------------------
' Relationships
'---------------------

WebPortal "1" --> "*" Building : contains
Building "1" --> "*" Entry : has
Building "1" --> "*" Image : has
User "1" --> "*" Building : owns
User "1" --> "*" Comment : writes
Administrator "1" --> "*" User : manages
Building "1" --> "*" Comment : has

'---------------------
' Use Cases & Actors
'---------------------

actor Visitor
actor User
actor Administrator

usecase "Register as User" as UC1
usecase "Activate Account via Email" as UC2
usecase "Login" as UC3
usecase "Create Building" as UC4
usecase "Manage Entries for Building" as UC5
usecase "Add Additional Entry" as UC6
usecase "Comment on Building" as UC7
usecase "Search Buildings" as UC8
usecase "Delete Comment" as UC9
usecase "Set Up User Accounts" as UC10

Visitor --> UC1 : Register
UC1 --> UC2 : Confirmation required
UC2 --> UC3 : After activation
User --> UC3 : Login
User --> UC4 : Create Building
User --> UC5 : Manage Entries
User --> UC6 : Add Entry
User --> UC7 : Comment
Visitor --> UC8 : Search
Administrator --> UC9 : Delete Comment
Administrator --> UC10 : Set Up Users

' Generalizations
UC1 <|-- UC2
UC3 <|-- UC4
UC3 <|-- UC5
UC3 <|-- UC6
UC3 <|-- UC7
UC3 <|-- UC8
UC3 <|-- UC9
UC3 <|-- UC10
@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Elements

- **Classes**: Defined with attributes like `Building`, `User`, `Entry`, etc.
- **Inheritance**: `TextEntry` and `NumericEntry` inherit from `Entry`.
- **Relationships**:
  - A `WebPortal` contains multiple `Building`s.
  - Each `Building` belongs to one `User` and has multiple `Entry`s and `Image`s.
  - `User` can create and manage `Comment`s.
  - `Administrator` inherits from `User` and has an `idCardNumber`.
- **Use Cases**:
  - Generalized around the main actions users can perform.
  - Includes user registration, login, commenting, searching, and administrative tasks.
  - `UC1` (`Register as User`) leads to `UC2` (`Activate Account via Email`) which is required before logging in.

